<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1911/525078.jpg" alt="#Newsmaker: Harmony Katulondi on his new gig as host of The Taste Master" width="350" height="407"> The show will feature aspiring, undiscovered chefs, who are invited to audition for the gig of a lifetime. South Africa’s hottest culinary professionals will be put to the test with a series of gruelling tasks that will test their limits as they battle it out in the hopes of becoming the resident chef on the channel’s popular variety show, Afternoon Express.This will be Katulondi’s first solo presenting gig. Here, he lets us in on what excites him most about this new career opportunity and how it feels to be part of The Taste Master team. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important}Congrats on the new show. How do you feel about it?Thank you, I’m pretty excited! Firstly because I love food and secondly because I get to be a part of making someone's dream come true. It's also such an honour to be hosting the show, and I know we're going to have a great time! .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important}Why do you think this show was needed and why did you want to be a part of it?Giving opportunities to people and opening up the industry is always needed. And the best part is that everyone who's part of the show will be put through challenges – which put the contestants in positions where their skills and talents are pushed to the next level. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important}What excites you most about this show?Apart from the food? Seeing people's passions and gifts come to life as they strive to become the ultimate taste master and get a place on Afternoon Express as the new resident foodie. I'm most excited to see someone achieve their dream! .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important}What do you love most about your career?What I love most about my career is the fact that I'm in a position that inspires and motivates people. I'm in a career where I can more positively impact and influence others. I also get to experience what the world has to offer and bring you insights into the lives of those who started out from different backgrounds and managed to turn their circumstances into success. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important}Any career highlights you’re particularly proud of?Some of my highlights include, winning the Presenter Search On 3 and becoming a Top Billing presenter. <img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1808/452683-120x120.jpg?2" alt="This year's top ten finalists for the Presenter Search on 3." width="120" height="120">Secrets to success on the 'Presenter Search on 3'!I met the new fixtures of the SABC3 family at an exclusive media event held at Expresso Studios in Sea Point earlier this week. It was quite something to be right there where some of the magic happens, but also seeing the new presenters sparkling in their element...By Leigh Andrews 10 Aug 2018Making it into the Forbes 30 under 30 in 2019. Co-writing a script for a short film and it winning a Safta, being part of Marvel’s Black Panther movie campaign and working with incredible brands.         View this post on Instagram           ... And then God decides to show off... Crazy thing is that He ain't even done yet... . �� @michael_mbaya �� @mamanphilodesigns . @forbesafrica @forbes @forbesunder30 #Forbes #forbes30under30 #forbes30MeetUp #forbeslist #ForbesAfrica #forbesafricaunder30 #forbesafrique #forbesmagazine #forbesunder30 #forbescover #africanmodel #africaninspired #Drc #congo #AfricanCasual #africanTravel #africancouture #TravelAfrica #SeeAfrica #africanmodel #AfricanPrint #Couture #africanstyle #africanfashion #africanclothing #africanbeauty #africandesigns #fashion @focusambassadors @africacreativecities @wesokoafrika @okayafrica @leaderscongo @congolesefashionbloggers @congotoglobal @congolese_onpoint @congoinsa @congopositif @voiceofcongo @congoamerica @congotoglobal @expressosh